  "prompt": "Why does my life suck so bad?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry to hear that you're feeling this way. It's important to remember that everyone goes through tough times, and it's okay to seek help and support when you need it. Here are a few steps that might help:\n\n1. **Talk to someone**: Whether it's a friend, family member, or mental health professional, sharing your feelings can be incredibly helpful.\n\n2. **Identify the issues**: Try to pinpoint what's causing you to feel this way. Identifying the root cause can help you figure out how to address it.\n\n3. **Self-care**: Make sure you're taking care of your physical and mental health. This includes eating well, getting enough sleep, exercising, and engaging in activities that you enjoy.\n\n4. **Set small goals**: Sometimes, setting small, achievable goals can help you regain a sense of control and accomplishment.\n\n5. **Seek professional help**: If your feelings persist or worsen, it might be helpful to speak to a therapist or counselor who can provide you with strategies and support.\n\nRemember, you're not alone, and there are people and resources out there to help you through this.",
